{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> πέψις</b>, εως, <br /> <i>Ionic dialect</i> ιος, ἡ, (πέσσω) <b>softening, ripening</b>, or <b>changing</b> by means of heat [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"(4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Meteorologica” 379b18, “GA” 775a17, “Pr.” 907a18): \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__I</b></Level2> of fruit, πέπανσίς ἐστιπ. τις [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “Mete.” 380a11, compare 4th-3rd c.BC: Theophrastus Philosophus “Historia Plantarum” 1.12.2, 5.1.3 (_plural_). \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <b>cooking</b> of food, including both ἕψησις and ὄπτησις (cooking by water or by dry heat), [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Meteorologica” 380b13, 381a23 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; κλίβανος καιόμενος εἰς π. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" LXX.Hos.7.4. \">LXX</a>]<br /><Level4><b>__II.b</b></Level4> <b>largess of cooked food,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" Inscriptiones Graecae ad res Romanas pertinentes 4.1637 (from Philadelphia). \">Refs</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.2</b></Level3> of wine, <b>fermentation</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus 2.656a. \">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__III</b></Level2> in Medicine texts, <b>digestion</b> of food, ὁμοία ἑψήσει [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Meteorologica” 381b7, compare “PA” 650a4, +others; τὰ τῆς π. ὄργανα 2nd c.AD: Galenus Medicus “περὶ φυσικῶν δυνάμεων - Scripta Minora” 1.10; π. καὶ ἀνάδοσις 3rd c.AD: Porphyrius Tyrius Philosophus “de Abstinentia - Porphyrii Opuscula” 1.45: _plural_, 2nd c.BC: Agatharchides Geographus 77. \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__III.2</b></Level3> <b>ripening, 'concoction'</b> of acrid humours, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Hippocrates Medicus “περὶ ἀρχαίης ἰητρικῇς” 18, compare 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus 2.102a. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level4><b>__III.2.b</b></Level4> <b>concoction</b>, as a function of the animal organs, ἡ τοῦ σπέρματος π. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “de Generatione Animalium” 719b2; ἡ διάκρισις π. ἐστί [prev. work] 775a17 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; of milk, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"[prev. work] 776b35. \">Refs</a>]","strongNumber":"G8786","accentedUnicode":"πέψις","shortDef":"baking","mediumDef":"baking","stepGloss":"baking","stepTransliteration":"pepsis","count":0,"_step_Type":"word"}]}